graph TB
    accTitle: CharLib Flow
    accDescr {
        CharLib's internal execution process, starting with YAML configuration input and resulting
        in a Liberty file. CharLib reads simulation settings and a list of cells from the YAML
        configuration. Cell SPICE netlists and SPICE transistor models are read from each cell
        entry. Next, cells are analysed to determine which measurement procedures need to be run.
        Once all cells are analysed, all procedures are executed in parallel as subprocesses.
        Finally, CharLib collects results and produces an output Liberty file.
    }
    docs@{shape: doc, label: "YAML Configuration"}
    docs --> config
    config[Load Configuration]
    config --> settings
    config --> cells
    config --> netlists
    config --> models
    settings[Simulation Settings]
    settings --> procedures
    cells@{shape: bow-rect, label: "List of Cells"}
    cells --> analysis
    netlists@{shape: docs, label: "SPICE Netlists"}
    netlists --> analysis
    models@{shape: docs, label: "Transistor Models"}
    models --> analysis
    subgraph analysis [Cell Analysis]
        validate_net{Is cell SPICE valid?}
        validate_net -->|Yes| stimulus
        validate_net -->|No| check_omit
        check_omit{Omit invalid cells?}
        check_omit -->|Yes| skip
        check_omit -->|No| error
        skip[Skip cell]
        error@{shape: dbl-circ, label: "Error"}
        stimulus[Generate test vectors]
        stimulus --> prepare
        prepare[Prepare measurement procedures]
    end
    analysis --> procedures
    procedures@{shape: subproc, label: "Run Procedures"}
    procedures --> results
    results[Collect Results]
    results --> output
    output([Liberty File])
